        },
        {
            "id": 1,
            "parent": 2,
            "text": "Widely used in speech and language processing , \r",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 2,
            "parent": 5,
            "text": "Kneser-Ney ( KN ) smoothing has consistently been shown to be one of the best-performing smoothing methods . <S>\r",
            "relation": "BACKGROUND"
        },
        {
            "id": 3,
            "parent": 2,
            "text": "However , KN smoothing assumes integer counts , \r",
            "relation": "CONTRAST"
        },
        {
            "id": 4,
            "parent": 3,
            "text": "limiting its potential uses\u2014for example , inside Expectation-Maximization . <S>\r",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 5,
            "parent": 0,
            "text": "In this paper , we propose a generalization of KN smoothing \r",
            "relation": "ROOT"
        },
        {
            "id": 6,
            "parent": 5,
            "text": "that operates on fractional counts , or , more precisely , on distributions over counts . <S>\r",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 7,
            "parent": 5,
            "text": "We rederive all the steps of KN smoothing to operate on count distributions instead of integral counts , \r",
            "relation": "EVALUATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 8,
            "parent": 7,
            "text": "and apply it to two tasks \r",
            "relation": "JOINT"
        },
        {
            "id": 9,
            "parent": 8,
            "text": "where KN smoothing was not applicable before : \r",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 10,
            "parent": 9,
            "text": "one in language model adaptation , and the other in word alignment . <S>\r",
            "relation": "EXEMPLIFICATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 11,
            "parent": 5,
            "text": "In both cases , our method improves performance significantly . <S>\r",
            "relation": "EVALUATION"
        }
    ]
}